---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';

export const title = "Sanford Dispensary Guide";
---

<Layout 
  title="Sanford Dispensary Guide | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Complete guide to opening a cannabis dispensary in Sanford, Maine. Market analysis, regulations, and investment requirements."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500916434205-0c77489c6cf7?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Sanford Dispensary Guide</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">How to open a cannabis dispensary in Sanford, Maine</p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>Sanford, Maine's eleventh-largest city with 21,000+ residents, is the largest city in York County and serves as a regional hub in southern Maine. Known for its growing tech manufacturing sector and historic downtown, Sanford presents an exciting opportunity for cannabis entrepreneurs seeking to serve an underserved market. Before moving forward, familiarize yourself with the <a href="/guides/maine-cannabis-real-estate/">real estate requirements</a> essential for success.</p>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Sanford: A Local Opportunity" type="passion">
      Operating in Sanford is more than just a business; it's about becoming a pillar of the community. Focus on local engagement and education to build lasting trust with your neighbors.
    </Callout>


    <section>
      <h2>Why Sanford?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>York County Hub</strong> - Largest city in the county</li>
        <li><strong>Growing Tech Sector</strong> - Young professional demographic</li>
        <li><strong>Underserved Market</strong> - Few dispensaries in area</li>
        <li><strong>Regional Draw</strong> - Serves surrounding towns</li>
        <li><strong>Affordable Costs</strong> - Lower than Portland</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Sanford Market</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Factor</th><th>Assessment</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Population</td><td>21,000+</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Regional Draw</td><td>50,000+</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Competition</td><td>Low</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Real Estate</td><td>Affordable ($12-18/sq ft)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Access</td><td>I-95, Route 109</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Local Regulations</h2>
      <p>Under <a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/rules" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Maine OCP regulations</a>, Sanford operators must:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Obtain state license from Maine Office of Cannabis Policy</li>
        <li>Verify local zoning allows cannabis operations</li>
        <li>Complete all compliance requirements</li>
        <li>Ensure employee authorizations are obtained</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Best Locations</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Main Street</strong> - Historic downtown</li>
        <li><strong>Route 109</strong> - High traffic corridor</li>
        <li><strong>Washington Street</strong> - Commercial zone</li>
        <li><strong>Industrial areas</strong> - Zoned for business</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Investment Requirements</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Category</th><th>Estimated Cost</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Real Estate (lease)</td><td>$2,000-3,500/mo</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Build-out</td><td>$80,000-150,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Total <a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-costs/">Investment</a></td><td>$320,000-550,000</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Further Reading</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/rules" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Maine Cannabis Rules</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>This is for informational purposes only and does not constitute legal or financial advice. Consult with qualified professionals.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
</style>
